{{Spanish name|Mina|Lorenzo}}
'''Santiago 'Santi' Mina Lorenzo''' (born 7 December 1995) is a Spanish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Celta de Vigo]] as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].

==Club career==
Born in [[Vigo]], [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]], Mina played youth football with hometown's [[Celta de Vigo]], and made his senior debuts with [[Celta de Vigo B|the reserves]] in the [[2012<U+2013>13 Tercera Divisi<U+00F3>n|2012<U+2013>13 season]], in [[Tercera Divisi<U+00F3>n]]. On 5 January he signed a professional deal with the club, running until 2018.<ref>[http://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/celta/2013/01/05/celta-blinda-santi-mina/0003_201301V5P42992.htm El Celta blinda a Santi Mina (Celta shields Santi Mina)]; [[La Voz de Galicia]], 5 January 2013 {{es icon}}</ref> 

Mina made his first-team <U+2013> and [[La Liga]] <U+2013> debut for them on 16 February 2013, coming on as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Iago Aspas]] in the 66th minute of a 1<U+2013>3 away defeat against [[Getafe CF]].<ref>[http://espnfc.com/en/report/348291/report.html?soccernet=true&cc=null Celta stay in drop zone after defeat]; [[ESPN FC]], 16 February 2013</ref> He scored his first top flight goal on 16 September, but in a 2<U+2013>3 loss at [[Athletic Bilbao]];<ref>[http://espnfc.com/en/report/373178/report.html?soccernet=true&cc=3888 Athletic open stadium with win]; ESPN FC, 16 September 2013</ref> at only 17 years, 9 months and 10 days, he became the team's youngest goalscorer in the first division.<ref>[http://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/celta/2013/09/17/santi-mina-convierte-goleador-joven-celta-primera-division/00031379370305112944694.htm Santi Mina se convierte en el goleador m<U+00E1>s joven del Celta en Primera Divisi<U+00F3>n (Santi Mina becomes the youngest goalscorer of Celta in first division)]; La Voz de Galicia, 17 September 2013 {{es icon}}</ref>

On 11 April 2015, Mina scored four goals in a 6<U+2013>1 home routing of [[Rayo Vallecano]],<ref>[http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2014_15/la-liga/jornada_31/cel_ray/ El Celta halla una Mina (Celta finds a Mine ("Mina" in English))]; [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]], 11 April 2015 {{es icon}}</ref> becoming the youngest player ever to do so in [[Spanish football league system|the main category of Spanish football]] and the first from Celta since 1979.<ref>[http://www.marca.com/2015/04/12/futbol/equipos/celta/1428795638.html <U+00A1>Cuatro goles de Santi Mina! (Four goals from Santi Mina!)]; Marca, 12 April 2015 {{es icon}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Mina's father, also named Santiago, was also a footballer. A [[Defender (association football)|defender]], he played for several clubs in the 70s/80s, including Celta.<ref>[http://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/gradario/2015/04/15/santi-mina-padre-me-visto-jugar/0003_201504V15P41992.htm Santi Mina: <U+00AB>Mi padre no me ha visto jugar<U+00BB> (Santi Mina: <U+00AB>My father has not seen me play<U+00BB>)]; La Voz de Galicia, 15 April 2015 {{es icon}}</ref><ref>[http://www.marca.com/2015/04/15/futbol/equipos/celta/1429095506.html 'Pap<U+00E1>' Mina no va a Bala<U+00ED>dos ('Daddy' Mina does not go to Bala<U+00ED>dos)]; Marca, 15 April 2015 {{es icon}}</ref>

